`expectEqual` returns an error union (`!void`), not `void`. In Zig, you cannot ignore error unions — you must handle them. In test blocks, the fix is to prepend `try`:

```zig
try expectEqual('a', c.base);
try expectEqual(Diacritic.empty, c.diacritic);
try expectEqual(Tone.level, c.tone);
```

This lets the test fail with a proper error message if the values don't match. Want me to apply the fix?
